{"text": " One of the things that Guatemala is well known for is their amazing coffee, so today I'm at a coffee farm and we're going to take a tour. Located on the outskirts of Antigua, Guatemala lies a hidden gem, Finka la Azotea. They offer daily coffee tours here, not only teaching about the history of coffee and how it became loved worldwide, but also the process in which it goes from their farm to your cup. After learning a bit about the history behind the coffee plants and how they became loved worldwide, then you get to head out into their very own farm and see all the coffee plants in person for yourself. And at this point in the tour, they also let everyone pick one of the coffee cherries so that you can taste it for yourself. When the coffee cherries are nice and dark red like this, they're sweet on the inside and when you spit out the seeds, those are the coffee beans that we know and love. After that, you'll walk through the rest of the tour learning how they ferment the coffee beans, then drive them out in the sun, remove the parchment layer, and finally roast them to be the perfect light, medium, or dark roast coffee that you know and love. And then after you've learned about the hard work and process that goes into making this incredible coffee, then you finally get to try it. So if you visit Antigua Guatemala, I would highly recommend booking a coffee tour with Finka de Asotea. And until next time, get outside and see what you can find.", "segments": [{"id": 0, "seek": 0, "start": 0.0, "end": 3.2, "text": " One of the things that Guatemala is well known for is their amazing coffee,", "tokens": [50364, 1485, 295, 264, 721, 300, 43120, 307, 731, 2570, 337, 307, 641, 2243, 4982, 11, 50524], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18912673607850686, "compression_ratio": 1.8125, "no_speech_prob": 0.047380030155181885}, {"id": 1, "seek": 0, "start": 3.2, "end": 5.5200000000000005, "text": " so today I'm at a coffee farm and we're going to take a tour.", "tok